      "description": "Available is a mechanically sorted BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six equipped with individual throttle bodies and double VANOS variable valve timing. Power is delivered through a tactile 6-speed manual transmission to a factory limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal traction and corner-exit speeds. This example has been proactively maintained with subframe reinforcement and a cooling system overhaul to preserve chassis rigidity and thermal efficiency. The suspension utilizes a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear arrangement, providing the precise turn-in and lateral stability expected of an M-division icon. While the exterior shows minor age-appropriate patina, the drivetrain remains robust and the engine pulls strongly to its 8,000 RPM redline. A compelling, driver-quality example for the purist.",
